definitions.definition: That lives in the sea and breeds in fresh water .
examples: Shads and most species of salmon are anadromous .

definitions.definition: Of a fern : in which the first veins in a frond segment are produced towards the apex of the frond.

main_definition: ( of a migratory fish ) That lives in the sea and breeds in fresh water .
secondary_definitions: ( botany ) Of a fern : in which the first veins in a frond segment are produced towards the apex of the frond.
